A sinus infection caused Elizabeth Taylor to be hospitalized on 9
April. She was admitted to the Daniel Freeman Marine Hospital in Santa
Monica, but yesterday she was transferred to St. John's Hospital and
Health Center because of a persistent fever and pneumonia. She is
being treated intravenously with antibiotics. Calls to the hospital
are being referred to the New York City firm that handles Ms. Taylor's
public relations. A spokeswoman there said only that Taylor's
condition had stabilized. The actress said that she had been advised
to remain in the hospital, and that she expected a full
recovery.</SUM>

<SUM
