SUMMARIZER="C">     

The Los Angeles District Attorney's office has declined to press
charges against several doctors who had allegedly over-prescribed
painkillers for Elizabeth Taylor. The announcement came Friday as the
investigation into the charges ended. The District Attorney's office
said that the prescribing procedures fell below the accepted medical
standard, but refused to charge the physicians with criminal
intent. The report said that one doctor had repeatedly tried to
convince Ms. Taylor to enter a rehabilitation center.  Taylor rejected
that, but eventually acknowledged a 35-year addiction to pills and
alcohol, and entered the Betty Ford Clinic in Rancho Mirage.</SUM>

<SUM
