Elizabeth Taylor was moved into intensive care at St John's Hospital
on Friday. Hospital officials said that her condition was stabilizing
after a biopsy was taken to determine the cause of the severe
pneumonia. She has been put on a ventilator to assist her breathing.
Her doctors said that she was seriously ill, but that they were
pleased with her progress. A spokeswoman said that her family was with
her, but that too much should not be read into that, and that
Ms. Taylor was not on her deathbed.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d24"
TYPE="PERDOC"
