SUMMARIZER="C">     

Elizabeth Taylor underwent a lung biopsy on Monday to further
determine the cause of her pneumonia. A prominent pulmonary specialist
who is not involved in caring for Ms.  Taylor said that the taking of
a biopsy was a prudent measure and one that will guide her doctors in
setting the course of her therapy. Taylor is now 58 years old. In 1961
she suffered a near-fatal bout with pneumonia. The same pulmonary
specialist cited above said that her history suggests that there may
be a basic problem with her lung structure or function.</SUM>

<SUM
