SUMMARIZER="C">     

Earlier this week Elizabeth Taylor's publicist said that the
Oscar-winning actress was improving and would soon be released from
the hospital. Ms. Taylor won Oscars for her performances in
"Butterfield 8" and "Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?". Since that
announcement recovery of the actress was dealt a setback when she
contracted bacterial pneumonia and developed a yeast infection that
will keep her hospitalized for another six weeks. She is now occupying
one of the hospital's suites. Her four children have visited her
throughout her hospitalization. Michael Jackson has also paid a
visit.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d24"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="AP900512-0038"
SELECTOR="D"
SUMMARIZER="C">     

Doctors treating Elizabeth Taylor said on Friday that her steady
recovery from viral pneumonia had been interrupted by bacterial
pneumonia and a yeast infection. The actress was admitted to Daniel
Freeman Marina Hospital on April 9th, suffering from a severe sinus
infection. She was transferred to St. John's Hospital and Health
Center when her condition deteriorated. Doctors later revealed that
she was near death on April 22nd.  The secondary bacterial pneumonia
often follows viral pneumonia. Her condition is now improving bur she
is expected to remain in the hospital for some time.</SUM>

