Actress Elizabeth Taylor and the National Enquirer have reached a
settlement of Ms.  Taylor's lawsuit against the tabloid. Taylor sought
damages of 20 million dollars for two articles published by the
Enquirer in June 1990 that reported on Taylor's medical problems and
her drinking when pneumonia caused her lengthy
hospitalization. Neither side discussed the terms of the agreement,
but Taylor's attorney said it was large enough that a trial should not
be pursued. The tabloid also apologized, saying that after seeing all
of Taylor's medical records, it was evident that inaccurate
information had been published. Taylor said that she felt "completely
vindicated".</SUM>
